				{
					"id": "RXoxpdtZNVgAZ8vv",
					"name": "Tactics",
					"description": "The dwarfs will try to stay behind the brambles and attack over them.\n\nThe radenwight bruxers will each move to one end of the brambles to try and keep the heroes contained.\n\nThe leader will roam and operate as a tactician.  Keeping at range, and defending the dwarfs if a hero escapes the bruxers.\n\nOn the third round, and anytime a hero is dying or dead, the leader will offer surrender and capture as an option.  If the heroes refuse, they will offer that if they leave now their fried will be spared."
				},
				{
					"id": "0e5bb2da-8bce-4d32-bc13-f5b9a17b02ae",
					"name": "Diminish Numbers",
					"description": "\nThe bandits will retreat if they lose the leader, both bruxers, or all of the dwarfs.\n\n### Difficulty Modifier\n\nThis objective doesn’t modify the encounter’s difficulty.\n\n### Success Condition\n\nDefeat all emenies, or force them to retreat.\n\n### Failure Condition\n\nHeroes are defeated.  In which case they are captured and taken to Blackhill.\n\n### Victories\n\n1 victory if the Bandits retreat.\n\n2 victories if all enemies are defeated."
				}
